      "writtenOn": "2020-06-12T19:53:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We don\u0027t *need* it as long as this is the only child, but if we ever ended up extending this effect to have a second child, we would need to keep track of the FP index for each child. Explicitly holding on to the FP indices feels safer and more general-case to me. This is also how generated FP code looks, and there\u0027s an advantage IMO to keeping the hand-written FP code looking and feeling like the gencode. But if you think I\u0027m being overly paranoid, I can remove it and just rely on the child count.",
      "parentUuid": "e256daae_9799a69e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 439,
        "startChar": 0,
